In anatomical position:
the palm of the hand faces forward and the dorsum of the hand faces backward;
the thumb is on the lateral aspect of the hand and the little finger is on its medial aspect;
the thumb and fingers are extended fully.
Abduction / adduction of the fingers occurs relative to the middle finger. The fingers stay in the plane of the hand. Flexion curls fingers into the palm; decreasing the angle of the MCPs, PIPs and DIPs. Extension straightens the fingers increasing the angle of these joints.
